The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques, specifically in the area of transition-based AMR parsing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of reinforcement learning (RL) also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a likely category. The paper also involves the use of attention mechanisms and contextualized embeddings, which are common in deep learning and neural networks, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. The use of named entities and concept identification suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the parser's performance, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible category.
